FBIS3-15355 "drsov043_e_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Ukraine, Bulgaria Sign Documents on Ties LD0203191494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1700 GMT 2 Mar 94 LD0203191494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] The signing of a protocol on exchanging ratification documents of the treaty on friendly relations and cooperation between Ukraine and the Republic of Bulgaria took place at Ukraine's Ministry of Foreign Affairs on 2 March. The treaty was signed in Sofia on 5 October 1992. Valentyn Lipatov, deputy minister of foreign affairs, signed the protocol for Ukraine, and Petur Markov, Bulgaria's ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary, signed it for Bulgaria.
